1689.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fone-killed-in-russian-missile-strike-on-east-ukraine-town%2Famp_articleshow%2F105231689.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fone-killed-in-russian-missile-strike-on-east-ukraine-town%2Famp_articleshow%2F105231689.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20India-Canada%20Ties%20-%20Vienna%20Convention%20And%20Diplomatic%20Obfuscation%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20friction%20in%20India-Canada%20ties%20continues%20over%20the%20allegations%20by%20Prime%20Minister%20Justin%20Trudeau%20that%20%26quot%3Bagents%20of%20the%20Indian%20government%26quot%3B%20were%20involved%20in%20the%20killing%20of%20Khalistan%20terrorist%20Hardeep%20Singh%20Nijjar%20in%20Surrey%2C%20British%20Columbia.%20The%20row%20resurfaced%20last%20week%20with%20US%20Secretary%20of%20State%20Antony%20Blinken%20saying%20he%20raised%20the%20issue%20with%20his%20Indian%20counterpart%20S%20Jaishankar%20in%20New%20Delhi%20while%20traveling%20for%20the%202%2B2%20meeting.%20Soon%2C%20Justin%20Trudeau%20not%20only%20brought%20up%20the%20matter%20of%20investigations%20into%20the%20killing%20while%20addressing%20the%20press%20but%20also%20the%20%26quot%3Bviolation%20of%20the%20Vienna%20Convention%26quot%3B%20of%20Diplomatic%20Relations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20backdrop%20of%20the%20Nijjar%20case%20the%20treatment%20of%20diplomats%20and%20the%20modalities%20of%20how%20countries%20maintain%20diplomatic%20ties%20through%20their%20representatives%20has%20also%20come%20into%20sharp%20focus.%20While%20it%20may%20appear%20that%20both%20sides%20are%20addressing%20the%20same%20issue%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20New%20Delhi%20and%20Ottawa%20seem%20to%20be%20raising%20different%20points%20under%20the%20same%20convention.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20India%20has%20used%20the%20term%20%26quot%3Bparity%26quot%3B%20in%20diplomatic%20presence%20as%20the%20keyword%20to%20argue%20its%20point%2C%20Canada%20has%20raised%20concerns%20over%20the%20%26quot%3Brevoking%20of%20diplomatic%20immunity%26quot%3B%20of%20its%20personnel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20let%20us%20elaborate%20on%20India's%20%26quot%3Bretaliation%26quot%3B%2C%20which%20Trudeau%20called%20the%20%26quot%3Bkicking%20out%26quot%3B%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Bwhole%20bunch%20of%20Canadian%20diplomats%26quot%3B.%20A%20statement%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20said%20there%20was%20a%20%26quot%3Bmuch%20higher%20number%20of%20Canadian%20diplomats%20in%20India%26quot%3B%2C%20and%20stressing%20it%20warranted%20%26quot%3Bparity%20in%20mutual%20diplomatic%20presence%20in%20New%20Delhi%20and%20Ottawa%2C%26quot%3B%20New%20Delhi%20asked%20Ottawa%20to%20withdraw%2041%20diplomats%20from%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20quoted%20Article%2011.1%20of%20the%20Vienna%20Convention%20on%20Diplomatic%20Relations%20to%20respond%20to%20Canada.%20It%20says%2C%20%26quot%3B1.%20In%20the%20absence%20of%20specific%20agreement%20as%20to%20the%20size%20of%20the%20mission%2C%20the%20receiving%20State%20may%20require%20that%20the%20size%20of%20a%20mission%20be%20kept%20within%20limits%20considered%20by%20it%20to%20be%20reasonable%20and%20normal%2C%20having%20regard%20to%20circumstances%20and%20conditions%20in%20the%20receiving%20State%20and%20to%20the%20needs%20of%20the%20particular%20mission.%202.%20The%20receiving%20State%20may%20equally%2C%20within%20similar%20bounds%20and%20on%20a%20non-discriminatory%20basis%2C%20refuse%20to%20accept%20officials%20of%20a%20particular%20category.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20this%2C%20the%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20concluded%20that%20it%20rejected%20%26quot%3Bany%20attempt%20to%20portray%20the%20implementation%20of%20parity%20as%20a%20violation%20of%20international%20norms%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Canada%20hasn't%20really%20raised%20the%20issue%20of%20parity%20of%20diplomatic%20presence%20in%20its%20official%20statements.%20Rather%2C%20it%20has%20raised%20the%20issue%20of%20%26quot%3Brevoking%20of%20diplomatic%20immunity%26quot%3B%20as%20a%20violation%20under%20Vienna%20Convention.%20The%20number%20of%20personnel%20was%20cited%20by%20some%20media%20outlets%20in%20Canada%20off%20the%20record%20but%20not%20brought%20up%20in%20official%20government%20statements.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%20is%20what%20Justin%20Trudeau%20said%20in%20his%20statement%20on%20November%2012%20-%20%26quot%3BIndia's%20response%20is%20to%20kick%20out%20a%20whole%20bunch%20of%20Canadian%20diplomats%20by%20violating%20their%20rights%20under%20the%20Vienna%20convention.%20That%20is%20of%20concern%20to%20countries%20around%20the%20world%20because%20if%20a%20given%20country%20just%20decides%20that%20the%20diplomats%20of%20another%20country%20are%20no%20longer%20protected%20that%20makes%20international%20relations%20more%20dangerous.%26quot%3B%20He%20reiterated%20what%20Foreign%20Ministry%20Melanie%20Joly%20said%20while%20revealing%20on%20October%2019%20that%2041%20diplomats%20had%20been%20called%20back%20to%20Canada%20from%20India%20after%20their%20diplomatic%20immunity%20was%20revoked.%20%26quot%3BDiplomatic%20immunity%20keeps%20diplomats%20safe%20no%20matter%20where%20they%20are%20from%20and%20where%20they%20are%20sent%20to.%20Immunity%20allows%20diplomats%20to%20do%20their%20work%20without%20reprisal%20in%20the%20country%20they%20are%20in.%20They%20are%20the%20fundamental%20principles%20and%20only%20work%20if%20every%20country%20abides%20by%20the%20rules%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20had%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Add%20image%20caption%20here%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Add%20image%20caption%20here%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-10%2F7aio8c8o_justin-trudeau-reuters_625x300_20_October_23.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustin%20Trudeau%20had%20alleged%20that%20%26quot%3Bagents%20of%20the%20Indian%20government%26quot%3B%20were%20involved%20in%20the%20killing%20of%20Khalistan%20terrorist%20Hardeep%20Singh%20Nijjar%20in%20Surrey.%20(File)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArticles%2029-39%20broadly%20deal%20with%20the%20issue%20of%20immunity%20of%20diplomats%20to%20carry%20out%20their%20duties%20and%20the%20associated%20privilege%20extended%20to%20their%20families.%20Article%2029%20says%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20person%20of%20a%20diplomatic%20agent%20shall%20be%20inviolable.%20He%20shall%20not%20be%20liable%20to%20any%20form%20of%20arrest%20or%20detention.%20The%20receiving%20State%20shall%20treat%20him%20with%20due%20respect%20and%20shall%20take%20all%20appropriate%20steps%20to%20prevent%20any%20attack%20on%20his%20person%2C%20freedom%20or%20dignity.%26quot%3B%20Article%2037%20adds%2C%20%26quot%3BMembers%20of%20the%20service%20staff%20of%20the%20mission%20who%20are%20not%20nationals%20of%20or%20permanently%20resident%20in%20the%20receiving%20State%20shall%20enjoy%20immunity%20in%20respect%20of%20acts%20performed%20in%20the%20course%20of%20their%20duties%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECanada%20had%20expelled%20one%20Indian%20diplomat%20after%20the%20allegations%20by%20PM%20Trudeau%20on%20September%2018%20and%20India%20retaliated%20by%20expelling%20one%20Canadian%20diplomat%20immediately.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArticle%209%20of%20the%20Vienna%20Convention%20deals%20with%20this%20situation%20when%20it%20says%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20receiving%20State%20may%20at%20any%20time%20and%20without%20having%20to%20explain%20its%20decision%2C%20notify%20the%20sending%20State%20that%20the%20head%20of%20the%20mission%20or%20any%20member%20of%20the%20diplomatic%20staff%20of%20the%20mission%20is%20persona%20non%20grata%20or%20that%20any%20other%20member%20of%20the%20staff%20of%20the%20mission%20is%20not%20acceptable.%20In%20any%20such%20case%2C%20the%20sending%20State%20shall%2C%20as%20appropriate%2C%20either%20recall%20the%20person%20concerned%20or%20terminate%20his%20functions%20with%20the%20mission.%20A%20person%20may%20be%20declared%20non%20grata%20or%20not%20acceptable%20before%20arriving%20in%20the%20territory%20of%20the%20receiving%20State.%202.%20If%20the%20sending%20State%20refuses%20or%20fails%20within%20a%20reasonable%20period%20to%20carry%20out%20its%20obligations%20under%20paragraph%201%20of%20this%20article%2C%20the%20receiving%20State%20may%20refuse%20to%20recognize%20the%20person%20concerned%20as%20a%20member%20of%20the%20mission.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExternal%20Affairs%20Minister%20S%20Jaishankar%2C%20however%2C%20explained%20that%20apart%20from%20%26quot%3Bparity%26quot%3B%2C%20there%20were%20other%20concerns%20that%20spurred%20the%20decision%20to%20revoke%20immunity.%20%26quot%3BIn%20our%20case%2C%20we%20invoked%20parity%20because%20we%20had%20concerns%20about%20continuous%20interference%20in%20our%20affairs%20by%20Canadian%20personnel.%20We%20haven't%20made%20much%20of%20that%20public.%20My%20sense%20is%20over%20a%20period%20of%20time%20more%20stuff%20will%20come%20out%20and%20people%20will%20understand%20why%20we%20had%20the%20kind%20of%20discomfort%20with%20many%20of%20them%20which%20we%20did%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Trudeau%20government%20so%20far%20hasn't%20revealed%20what%20evidence%20it%20has%20on%20the%20alleged%20involvement%20of%20%26quot%3BIndian%20government%20agents%26quot%3B%20in%20Nijjar's%20killing%2C%20India%20too%20has%20not%20made%20public%20what%20it%20has%20on%20the%20%26quot%3Binterference%26quot%3B%20by%20%26quot%3BCanadian%20personnel%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Add%20image%20caption%20here%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Add%20image%20caption%20here%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-06%2Faei8mf7g_hardeep-singh-nijjar_625x300_19_June_23.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKhalistan%20terrorist%20Hardeep%20Singh%20Nijjar%20was%20killed%20in%20Surrey%2C%20British%20Columbia%20(File)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResponses%20to%20expulsion%20are%20often%20reciprocal%20and%20in%20equal%20measure.%20Expulsions%20or%20the%20recall%20of%20diplomats%20is%20often%20a%20result%20of%20a%20fallout%20between%20two%20nations.%20The%20issue%20can%20be%20escalated%20to%20the%20top%20level%20of%20diplomats%20too%2C%20as%20seen%20in%20the%20case%20of%20India%20and%20Pakistan.%20The%20two%20countries%20recalled%20their%20high%20commissioners%20in%202019%20as%20ties%20plummeted%20after%20the%20Pulwama%20terror%20attack.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20case%20of%20diplomatic%20immunity%20that%20had%20pushed%20India%20to%20react%20sharply%20to%20the%20US%20in%20the%20case%20of%20Indian%20officer%20Devyani%20Khobragade%20in%202013.%20The%20arrest%20of%20the%20then%20Deputy%20Consul%20General%20in%20New%20York%20and%20her%20harassment%20in%20custody%20was%20deplored%20by%20India%20as%20a%20clear%20violation%20of%20her%20diplomatic%20immunity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20as%20major%20differences%20persist%20between%20India%20and%20Canada%20over%20the%20Khalistan%20issue%2C%20the%20fact%20remains%20that%20while%20the%20two%20use%20diplomatic%20means%20to%20convey%20displeasure%2C%20it%20could%20lead%20to%20further%20complications%20and%20fallouts%20on%20both%20sides.%20The%20most%20significant%20being%20on%20visa-related%20issues%3B%20Canada%20in%20its%20statement%20on%20October%2019%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BUnfortunately%2C%20this%20mass%20expulsion%20will%20impact%20our%20operations%2C%20and%20client%20service%20will%20be%20affected.%20We%20will%20now%20be%20forced%20to%20pause%20temporarily%20all%20in-person%20services%20at%20Consulates%2C%20until%20further%20notice%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20said%20India's%20decision%20would%20impact%20the%20levels%20of%20services%20to%20citizens%20of%20both%20countries.%20%26quot%3BImmigration%2C%20Refugees%20and%20Citizenship%20Canada%20(IRCC)%20will%20continue%20to%20accept%20and%20process%20applications%20from%20India.%20However%2C%20certain%20application%20requirements%20will%20need%20to%20be%20completed%20locally%20or%20on-site%20in%20a%20secure%20environment.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20the%20reduction%20in%20the%20size%20of%20the%20IRCC%20team%20will%20affect%20service%20standards%20for%20residents%20of%20India%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20statement%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20sizeable%20population%20of%20India-origin%20people%20in%20Canada%2C%20with%202%2C30%2C000%20Indian%20students%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20aftermath%20of%20Trudeau's%20allegations%2C%20India%20had%20also%20suspended%20visa%20services%2C%20which%20were%20later%20resumed%20after%20approximately%20a%20month%20on%20October%2026.%20The%20visa%20service%20was%20resumed%20for%20four%20categories%20-%20Entry%20visa%2C%20Business%20Visa%2C%20Medical%20Visa%20and%20Conference%20Visa.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20highly%20interconnected%20world%2C%20diplomatic%20friction%20between%20countries%20immediately%20leads%20to%20consequences%20for%20the%20people%2C%20so%20a%20greater%20understanding%20of%20concerns%20by%20countries%20on%20sensitive%20issues%20and%20the%20ability%20of%20both%20sides%20to%20quietly%20resolve%20matters%20without%20them%20becoming%20political%20fodder%20on%20either%20side%20reflects%20diplomatic%20maturity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Maha%20Siddiqui%20is%20a%20journalist%20who%20has%20extensively%20reported%20on%20public%20policy%20and%20global%20affairs.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700038320000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-09%2F122o7v0g_modi-trudeau-afp_625x300_23_September_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Findia-canada-ties-vienna-convention-and-diplomatic-obfuscation-4575735%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20friction%20in%20India-Canada%20ties%20continues%20over%20the%20allegations%20by%20Prime%20Minister%20Justin%20Trudeau%20tha