%2F15103146%2FF-ruHCtXIAAf5jW.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202002%2C%20our%20professor%20took%20us%20to%20meet%20Dennis%20Ross%2C%20who%20had%20been%20the%20Middle%20East%20envoy%20under%20US%20President%20Bill%20Clinton%2C%20and%20presided%20over%20the%20failed%20Camp%20David%20Summit%20in%20July%202000%20between%20Israeli%20prime%20minister%20Ehud%20Barak%20and%20Palestinian%20leader%20Yasser%20Arafat.%20After%20the%20failure%20of%20the%20summit%2C%20both%20Clinton%20and%20Barak%20blamed%20Arafat%20for%20the%20failure.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20This%20exclusive%20nature%20of%20this%20blame%20was%20undercut%20by%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pbs.org%2Fwgbh%2Fpages%2Ffrontline%2Fshows%2Foslo%2Fnegotiations%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ETaba%20Summit%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20took%20place%20in%202001%2C%20in%20which%20the%20Israelis%20and%20Palestinians%20came%20tantalisingly%20close%20to%20a%20peace%20agreement%20before%20the%20election%20of%20Ariel%20Sharon%20as%20the%20new%20Israeli%20prime%20minister.%20Then%2C%20the%20Second%20Intifada%20swept%20aside%20any%20hopes%20of%20an%20agreement.%20At%20the%20Taba%20Summit%2C%20the%20Palestinians%20were%20allowed%20to%20negotiate.%20At%20Camp%20David%2C%20Arafat%20had%20merely%20been%20presented%20with%20a%20deal%2C%20told%20that%20it%20was%20the%20best%20the%20Palestinians%20could%20ever%20expect%2C%20and%20expected%20to%20sign%20it%20then%20and%20there.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20245px)%2085vw%2C%20245px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F15103644%2FLeader_of_the_PLO_Yasser_Arafat_1996_Dan_Hadani_Archive.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22245%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F15103644%2FLeader_of_the_PLO_Yasser_Arafat_1996_Dan_Hadani_Archive.jpg%20825w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F15103644%2FLeader_of_the_PLO_Yasser_Arafat_1996_Dan_Hadani_Archive-206x300.jpg%20206w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F15103644%2FLeader_of_the_PLO_Yasser_Arafat_1996_Dan_Hadani_Archive-704x1024.jpg%20704w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-684803%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22357%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EYasser%20Arafat.%20Gideon%20Markowiz%20%2F%20Photographer%3A%20Israel%20Press%20and%20Photo%20Agency%20(I.P.P.A.)%20%2F%20Dan%20Hadani%20collection%2C%20National%20Library%20of%20Israel%20%2F%20CC%20BY%204.0%2C%20CC%20BY%204.0%20%26lt%3Bhttps%3A%2F%2Fcreativecommons.org%2Flicenses%2Fby%2F4.0%3E%2C%20via%20Wikimedia%20Commons%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENews%20of%20the%20Taba%20Summit%20had%20largely%20vanished%20with%20the%20rise%20of%20Sharon%20%E2%80%93%20who%20had%20overseen%20the%20massacre%20of%20unarmed%20civilians%20after%20Palestinian%20fighters%20had%20been%20made%20to%20exit%20the%20Sabra%20and%20Shatila%20refugee%20camps%20in%20Lebanon%20by%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20Phalangist%20allies%20%E2%80%93%20and%20the%20Al%20Qaida%20attack%20of%20September%2011%2C%202001.%20Sharon%20was%20quick%20to%20denounce%20Arafat%20as%20%E2%80%9Cour%20bin%20Laden%E2%80%9D%2C%20much%20as%20the%20current%20Israeli%20government%20is%20comparing%20Hamas%20to%20ISIS.%20The%20US%2C%20under%20the%20George%20W.%20Bush%20administration%2C%20was%20happy%20to%20back%20Sharon.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERoss%20had%20retired%20from%20the%20government%2C%20and%20was%20at%20a%20new%20think%20tank%20as%20a%20prominent%20commentator%20on%20West%20Asia.%20He%20explained%20to%20us%20that%20Arafat%20had%20never%20truly%20pursued%20peace%2C%20and%20the%20test%20of%20it%20was%20the%20ability%20to%20crack%20down%20on%20Palestinian%20extremists.%20He%20told%20us%20an%20eloquent%20story%20of%20how%20he%20had%20been%20in%20the%20office%20with%20Yitzhak%20Rabin%20%E2%80%93%20the%20Israeli%20prime%20minister%20who%20signed%20the%20Oslo%20Accords%20with%20Arafat%20%E2%80%93%20when%20news%20of%20a%20terrorist%20attack%20had%20come.%20Rabin%2C%20Ross%20told%20us%2C%20then%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CArafat%20needs%20his%20Altalena.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Altalena%20was%20the%20name%20of%20a%20ship%20carrying%20military%20hardware%20worth%20millions%20donated%20by%20France%20for%20the%20Irgun%20%E2%80%93%20classified%20as%20a%20terrorist%20organisation%20by%20most%20including%20Jewish%20luminaries%20like%20Albert%20Einstein%20%E2%80%93%20due%20to%20arrive%20in%20Israel%20in%20June%201948%2C%20just%20after%20the%20new%20state%20had%20been%20created.%20David%20Ben%20Gurion%2C%20the%20Israeli%20prime%20minister%2C%20declared%20that%20the%20weapons%20would%20come%20to%20the%20Israeli%20Defence%20Forces%20or%20would%20be%20seized.%20The%20Irgun%20refused%2C%20and%20Ben%20Gurion%20ordered%20a%20raid%20on%20the%20ship.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERabin%20understood%20the%20significance%20of%20this%20more%20than%20most%2C%20Ross%20said%2C%20because%20he%20had%20commanded%20the%20raid%20on%20the%20Altalena.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20he%20finished%2C%20we%20were%20allowed%20to%20ask%20questions%2C%20and%20I%20asked%20him%20how%20he%20could%20compare%20the%20Altalena%20affair%20with%20Arafat%E2%80%99s%20situation%2C%20since%20the%20Altalena%20happened%20after%20Israel%20was%20founded.%20Ben%20Gurion%20never%20moved%20against%20the%20Irgun%20before%20that%2C%20so%20if%20they%20wanted%20Arafat%20to%20act%2C%20why%20not%20give%20the%20Palestinians%20the%20state%20they%20wanted%2C%20and%20then%20judge%20whether%20they%20could%20do%20an%20Altalena%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20I%20also%20asked%20whether%20it%20was%20only%20Arafat%E2%80%99s%20unwillingness%20to%20achieve%20peace%20that%20was%20a%20factor.%20Which%20Israeli%20PM%20had%20been%20serious%20about%20peace%3F%20Rabin%2C%20who%20said%20%E2%80%9CNo%20date%20is%20holy%E2%80%9D%20when%20refusing%20to%20hand%20over%20control%20in%20the%20Oslo%20Accords%3F%20Netanyahu%2C%20who%20had%20instigated%20the%20murder%20of%20Rabin%20for%20signing%20the%20Oslo%20Accords%3F%20Barak%2C%20who%20had%20double%20the%20pace%20of%20settlement%20expansion%20on%20stolen%20Palestinian%20land%3F%20Or%20Sharon%2C%20who%20was%20condemned%20by%20even%20the%20Israeli%20investigation%20for%20his%20role%20in%20the%20Sabra%20and%20Shatila%20massacre%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fwhy-israels-supporters-in-the-west-are-no-friends-of-jews%5C%22%3EWhy%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20Supporters%20in%20the%20West%20Are%20No%20Friends%20of%20Jewish%20People%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EInstead%20of%20replying%2C%20Ross%20left%2C%20much%20to%20the%20embarrassment%20of%20my%20professor%20and%20the%20confusion%20of%20the%20rest%20of%20us.%20My%20professor%20later%20explained%20that%20the%20Camp%20David%20fiasco%20had%20ended%20Ross%E2%80%99s%20career%2C%20and%20he%20personally%20blamed%20Arafat.%20All%20that%20might%20be%20true%2C%20but%20it%20had%20little%20to%20do%20with%20my%20query.%20Most%20of%20whose%20facts%20were%20from%20Israeli%20sources.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20mention%20this%20anecdote%20now%20because%20Ross%20is%20emblematic%20of%20the%20establishment%20position%20in%20the%20US.%20He%20served%20in%20very%20high%20profile%20roles%20in%20both%20Republican%20and%20Democratic%20administrations%2C%20and%20is%20seen%20as%20an%20important%20%E2%80%9Ccentrist%E2%80%9D%20voice%20in%20US%20Middle%20East%20policy%20circles.%20More%20importantly%2C%20Ross%E2%80%99s%20blindness%20to%20his%20assumptions%20%E2%80%93%20that%20the%20Israelis%20were%20seeking%20peace%20but%20had%20no%20partners%20%E2%80%93%20and%20his%20inability%20to%20reply%20to%20simple%20facts%2C%20is%20exactly%20the%20reason%20why%20the%20US%20finds%20itself%20embroiled%20in%20another%20stupid%20war%2C%20bleeding%20legitimacy%2C%20and%20unable%20to%20offer%20any%20reasonable%20way%20to%20ensure%20peace%20for%20the%20Palestinians%20or%20the%20Israelis.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20idiocy%20that%20the%20Israeli%20government%20knew%20exactly%20what%20it%20was%20doing%20was%20never%20so%20obvious%20as%20during%20the%20October%207%20attack%20by%20Hamas%2C%20killing%20more%20than%20a%20thousand%20people%2C%20mostly%20civilians.%20It%20was%2C%20after%20all%2C%20Netanyahu%20who%20had%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.timesofisrael.com%2Ffor-years-netanyahu-propped-up-hamas-now-its-blown-up-in-our-faces%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esupported%20Hamas%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20undercut%20the%20Palestinian%20Authority%20and%20destroy%20any%20negotiations.%20It%20was%20Netanyahu%20who%20has%20pushed%20forcefully%20for%20the%20Abraham%20Accords%20%E2%80%93%20agreements%20with%20Arab%20states%20without%20a%20Palestinian%20peace%20deal%20%E2%80%93%20which%20US%20president%20Donald%20Trump%20and%20now%20Joe%20Biden%20have%20supported.%20It%20was%20Netanyahu%E2%80%99s%20coalition%20members%20that%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.timesofisrael.com%2Fcoalition-mks-slam-shin-bets-warning-on-jewish-terror-gallant-insulting-comments%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eaccused%20its%20own%20intelligence%20chief%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%E2%80%93%20Ronan%20Bar%20of%20the%20Shin%20Bet%20%E2%80%93%20of%20confusing%20its%20citizens%20with%20its%20enemies%20when%20he%20tried%20to%20warn%20them%20that%20Jewish%20terrorism%20was%20creating%20a%20dangerous%20situation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%20yet%2C%20the%20US%20was%20so%20blind%20in%20its%20alliance%20that%20%E2%80%93%20according%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%93%20its%20intelligence%20agencies%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F10%2F29%2Fworld%2Fmiddleeast%2Fisrael-intelligence-hamas-attack.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehad%20ceased%20to%20gather%20information%20from%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20because%20they%20thought%20the%20Israelis%20had%20it%20all%20under%20control.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENow%20the%20same%20man%2C%20the%20same%20cabinet%2C%20that%20created%20these%20conditions%20in%20Israel%20is%20conducting%20an%20infinite%20war%2C%20which%20has%20consumed%20more%20than%2010%2C000%20Palestinian%20lives%20%E2%80%93%20again%20mostly%20of%20civilians.%20The%20US%20has%20offered%20unstinting%20financial%2C%20military%2C%20and%20diplomatic%20support.%20In%20return%20it%20has%20got%20nothing.%20No%20long-term%20plan%2C%20no%20real%20protection%20of%20civilians%2C%20not%20even%20a%20%E2%80%98thank%20you%E2%80%99%20postcard%20from%20Netanyahu.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20US%20is%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20ally.%20It%20is%20axiomatic%20that%20it%20should%20support%20Israel%2C%20but%20a%20stupid%20ally%20is%20no%20benefit%20to%20anybody.%20America%E2%80%99s%20assumption%20that%20Israel%20wants%20peace%20when%20the%20only%20governments%20that%20have%20come%20to%20power%20in%20Israel%20for%20decades%20are%20those%20that%20explicitly%20resist%20peace%2C%20is%20not%20just%20contrary%20to%20the%20facts%2C%20but%20so%20bizarrely%20outlandish%20that%20it%20convinces%20almost%20nobody%20else.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20The%20outcome%20is%20policies%20that%20help%20neither%20the%20US%20or%20Israel%2C%20and%20certainly%20not%20the%20Palestinians.%20But%20then%2C%20maybe%20the%20US%20does%20not%20even%20care.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20explicitly%20anti-Semitic%20politicians%20like%20Marjorie%20Taylor%20Greene%20are%20the%20%E2%80%9Cstrongest%20supporters%E2%80%9D%20of%20Israel%20in%20the%20US%2C%20you%20begin%20to%20wonder%20if%20the%20vanity%2