.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EShort-faced%20bears%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20saber-tooth%20cat%20and%20a%20short-faced%20bear%20roar%20at%20each%20other%20in%20an%20artist's%20rendering%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654d9942b788914e5553b655%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20short-faced%20bear%20was%20far%20larger%20than%20a%20grizzly%20when%20it%20stood%20on%20its%20hind%20legs.%3Cp%3EDaniel%20Eskridge%2FStocktrek%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHeight%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2011%20feet%20tall%20when%20standing%20on%20their%20hind%20legs%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWeight%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%201%2C500%20to%202%2C200%20pounds%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%20did%20they%20go%20extinct%3F%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EBetween%2012%2C7000%20and%2011%2C000%20years%20ago%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20years%20ago%2C%20the%20Arctodus%20simus%20cast%20a%20looming%20shadow%20over%20boreal%20forests%2C%20plains%2C%20tundra%2C%20grasslands%2C%20and%20subtropical%20woodlands.%20Known%20as%20the%20short-faced%20bear%2C%20it%20ranged%20across%20the%20US%20and%20Canada%2C%20into%20Florida.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20short-faced%20bears%20were%20huge%2C%26quot%3B%20Lindsey%20said.%20They%20were%20far%20larger%20than%208-foot-tall%20grizzly%20bears%20and%20%26quot%3Bwould've%20been%20terrifying.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStudies%20have%20shown%20that%20its%20muzzle%20was%20perhaps%20not%20as%20short%20as%20its%20name%20suggests.%20Some%20researchers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ficeage.museum.state.il.us%2Fmammals%2Fshort-faced-bear-0%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ealso%20think%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20bear%20may%20have%20been%20an%20omnivore%20instead%20of%20solely%20a%20meat%20eater.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EDire%20wolves%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20reconstuc