may%20have%20helped%20them%20survive%20a%20bit%20longer%20than%20many%20other%20mammals%20they%20lived%20alongside.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EAmerican%20lion%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Three%20lions%20crouch%20drinking%20from%20a%20pond%20in%20an%20artist's%20rendering%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654da15936d588dc55ce3ab8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22480%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAmerican%20lions%20were%20about%20as%20tall%20as%20modern%20lions%20but%20weighed%20much%20more.%3Cp%3ENational%20Park%20Service%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHeight%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%204%20feet%20at%20the%20shoulder%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWeight%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Up%20to%20770%20pounds%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%20did%20they%20go%20extinct%3F%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EBetween%2010%2C000%20and%2012%2C000%20years%20ago%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESaber-tooths%20weren't%20the%20only%20big%20cats%20that%20made%20their%20home%20in%20North%20America.%20Panthera%20atrox%20was%20one%20of%20the%20largest%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Emembers%20of%20the%20cat%20family%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eever.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fancient-american-lion-fossil-found-in-dried-up-mississippi-river-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmerican%20lions%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20huge%2C%26quot%3B%20Lindsey%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20much%2C%20much%20bigger%20than%20modern%20lions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20fairly%20rare%20in%20the%20fossil%20record%2C%20there's%20evidence%20the%20big%20cats%20did%20make%20their%20way%20throughout%20North%20America.%20Scientists%20have%20found%20their%20bones%20and%20teeth%20from%20Canada%20to%20Mexico.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fphys.org%2Fnews%2F2010-05-scientists-american-lion.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehave%20debated%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20whether%20these%20gigantic%20cats%20are%20more%20closely%20related%20to%20modern%20lions%20or%20jaguars.%20Its%20skull%20shares%20similarities%20with%20lions'%2C%20but%20its%20jaw%20resembles%20those%20of%20jaguars%20and%20tigers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDue%20to%20its%20enormous%20size%2C%20the%20American%20lion%20was%20able%20to%20make%20meals%20out%20of%20bison%20and%20wild%20horses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EAncient%20bison%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222218%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20mummified%20skull%20of%20an%20extinct%20bison%20behind%20a%20glass%20case%20at%20the%20Smithsonian%20Institution's%20National%20Museum%20of%20Natural%20History%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654da35cb788914e5553b8a1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20mummified%20remains%20of%20a%20steppe%20bison%2C%20Bison%20priscus%2C%20were%20found%20in%20present-day%20Alaska%20after%20it%20was%20preserved%20over%2028%2C000%20years%20ago.%3Cp%3EKatherine%20Frey%2FThe%20Washington%20Post%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHeight%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%207.5%20feet%20tall%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWeight%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%203%2C500%20pounds%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%20did%20they%20go%20extinct%3F%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ERoughly%2010%2C000%20years%20ago%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20the%20Camelops%20and%20horses%20that%20evolved%20in%20North%20America%2C%20other%20big%20beasts%20migrated%20in.%20That%20includes%20ancient%20bison.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20are%20the%20most%20recent%20arrivals%20into%20North%20America%20of%20all%20the%20Pleistocene%20megafauna%2C%26quot%3B%20Lindsey%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20bison%20species%20appeared%20around%203%20million%20years%20ago%20in%20South%20Asia%20and%20China.%20Eventually%2C%20some%20crossed%20the%20Bering%20Land%20Bridge.%20They%20start%20showing%20up%20in%20the%20North%20American%20fossil%20reco