through%20the%20threat%20of%20shutdowns%20of%20part%20of%20%5Bthe%5D%20government%20over%20and%20over%20again%2C%26quot%3B%20Collins%20said%2C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpunchbowl.news%2Farticle%2Fmike-johnson-shutdown-continuing-resolution%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20per%20Punchbowl%20News%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BSo%2C%20it%20doesn't%20seem%20to%20me%20to%20make%20a%20lot%20of%20sense.%20But%20I'm%20willing%20to%20hear%20more%20about%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESen.%20Chris%20Murphy%2C%20a%20Connecticut%20Democrat%2C%20said%20Johnson's%20approach%20sounded%20%26quot%3Bgimmicky%26quot%3B%20but%20he%20would%20be%20open%20to%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20White%20House%20deemed%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthehill.com%2Fhomenews%2Fhouse%2F4305757-white-house-reacts-speakers-stopgap-funding-bill%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ean%20%26quot%3Bunserious%20proposal.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20It's%20likely%20now%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20will%20sign%20it%20into%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20their%20criticism%2C%20some%20of%20these%20same%20lawmakers%20may%20vote%20for%20the%20plan.%20For%20Democrats%20especially%2C%20Johnson's%20plan%20comes%20without%20the%20poison%20pills%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmtg-greene-house-gop-holman-rule-one-dollar-salaries-biden-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eslashing%20a%20Cabinet%20secretary's%20salary%20to%20just%20%241%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20restricting%20access%20to%20abortions%20that%20often%20accompany%20bills%20that%20fund%20just%20the%20Pentagon%20or%20a%20collection%20of%20other%20departments.%20It's%20also%20the%20same%20strategy%20that%20helped%20lead%20to%20former%20Speaker%20Kevin%20McCarthy's%20historic%20ouster.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20its%20face%2C%20the%20plan%20avoids%20Congress'%20holiday%20tradition%20of%20ramming%20through%20hundred-page%20bills%20funding%20the%20government%20crammed%20with%20other%20unrelated%20measures%20all